VALUES (
  'The Financial Reality of Presales: Deposits, Hidden Costs, and GST',
  'presale-condo-bc-deposits-hidden-costs-gst',
  'How much deposit do you actually need? Do you pay GST on a presale? Uzair breaks down the exact numbers — deposit structures, closing costs, PTT exemptions, and the hidden costs that catch buyers off guard.',
  E'You know you want to get into the presale market, but the numbers are keeping you up at night. You are staring at your savings account, trying to figure out if you actually have the cash to pull the trigger.\n\nThe questions are constant: How much deposit is needed for a presale condo in BC? Do I need a mortgage right away? What are the exact closing costs, and do I have to pay GST on a new build?\n\nI am Uzair Muhammad, and I don''t sugar-coat the numbers. If you want to invest in Surrey or the Fraser Valley, you need to understand the exact financial reality of a presale transaction before you sign anything. This guide breaks down the hard data on deposits, hidden costs, and what you actually need to close the deal.\n\n## The Truth About Presale Deposits and Mortgages\n\nWhen you buy a presale condo in BC, you do not need a mortgage on day one. You are only responsible for the deposit structure outlined in your contract.\n\nHistorically, developers demanded a straight 20% deposit. Today, the market has shifted. Many developers in Surrey and Langley are offering extended deposit structures — sometimes 10% or 15% spread out over 18 to 24 months. You might pay 5% at signing, another 5% in six months, and the final 5% a year later.\n\n> You only need to secure your mortgage when the building is completed and you take possession. This gives you 2 to 4 years to save more cash, improve your credit score, or let your investments grow.\n\n## Why the Numbers Matter for Your Capital\n\nIf you are an investor, the deposit structure is your leverage. A 10% deposit on a $600,000 condo means you control a massive asset for just $60,000. If the market appreciates, your return on investment is calculated against that $60,000, not the full purchase price. But if you miscalculate the closing costs, that leverage can turn into a liability.\n\nIf you are a first-time buyer, understanding the deposit timeline is the only way to know if you can actually afford the unit. You need to know exactly when the developer will pull those funds so you aren''t caught scrambling for cash.\n\n> The biggest mistake buyers make is ignoring the hidden costs of buying a new construction condo. They budget for the down payment but forget about the taxes and fees due at completion.\n\n## How to Calculate Your Exact Costs\n\nHere is the financial breakdown you need to prepare for before buying a presale:\n\n1. **Map Your Deposit Structure:** How much deposit is needed for a presale condo in BC? It ranges from 10% to 20%. Demand a clear schedule from the developer and ensure you have the liquid cash available for each milestone.\n\n2. **Prepare for GST:** Do you pay GST on presale condos in BC? Yes. New construction is subject to 5% GST. If the purchase price is under $450,000 and you plan to live in it, you may qualify for a partial rebate. If you are an investor, you must pay the GST upfront, though you can often claim it back later if you rent the unit long-term.\n\n3. **Calculate Closing Costs:** What are the exact closing costs on a new build? Budget 1.5% to 2% of the purchase price for legal fees, appraisal fees, and strata move-in fees.\n\n4. **Factor in the Property Transfer Tax (PTT):** Unless you qualify for a first-time buyer or newly built home exemption, you will pay PTT (1% on the first $200,000, 2% on the balance up to $2,000,000).\n\n5. **Get Pre-Approved Early:** Do I need a mortgage right away for a presale? No, but you should get a pre-approval or a builder''s cap rate to protect yourself against rising interest rates between now and completion.\n\n## The Bottom Line\n\nThe financial reality of a presale is not a guessing game; it is a math equation. You do not need the full purchase price today, but you must have a bulletproof plan for your deposit milestones, the 5% GST, and your closing costs.\n\n> If you understand the numbers, a presale is one of the most powerful tools for building wealth in BC. If you ignore them, you will lose your capital.\n\n## Work With a Presale Specialist\n\nStop relying on rough estimates and start looking at the hard data. I am Uzair Muhammad, and I build exact financial models for my clients so they know their exact exposure before they sign a contract. Book a free strategy call with me today at presalewithuzair.com, and let''s run the numbers on your next investment.',
